Fertiliser: 400g
Yield:

1)Crush the fertiliser into a powder
2)dillute with water
3)filter the liquid with cotton
4)Put the non filtered liquid back into the container and dillute a second time with water then filter that again with cotton
5)filter the filtered liquid repeatedly until you get a clear solution
6)heat the liquid on a stove at level 5 heat for approx 5 hours
7)put the clean solution in a beaker and then put that in the fridge to then get a crystal formation of the ammonium nitrate 
8)put the crystal into a oven at 75 C for 3 hours
9)Fill a beaker with the ammonium nitrate and then pour 50ml of sulphuric acid into the beaker
